Comment: Looks like a fun movie, so what if he isn't a spitting image of Harrison Ford? They could have done his face with CGI but ya'll woulda complained about that too. "It doesn't feel like a Star Wars movie." I think that's a good thing, let's see the universe from a new perspective and tell new stories. Yeah it's expanding off of a character we already know and love, but at least it's a fresh take. They won't have to sit and reference the OT just to please fans. I think telling Solo's origin story is a great way to take the series to a new place while still having a tinge of familiarity to keep us grounded in the universe.

Title: Solo: A Star Wars Story Official Trailer
Comment:
Disney's Star Wars "side stories" are better than their main films because the characters are victims of probable, well-established circumstances and within these circumstances, they struggle to get through.
Whereas the main films operate out of geocentricity‚ÄîCharacters are walking deus ex machinas without credible ingenuity or skill, of which the world and all its events revolve around. 

Overpowered ‚â† Bad Storytelling. 
Overpowered characters are completely justified if focus is first attributed to world-building and the Magic Rules that world adheres to. Once the rules are established, characters can "rampage" to their heart's desire just as long as they stay within the limitations of the established rules (These are some of the best stories).

The problem of the main films isn't any one specific character but the failure to accurately set up circumstances that are believable irrespective to the "A-team" as well as failure to at least hint at lore rules before a feat is performed.

Title: Solo: A Star Wars Story Official Trailer
Comment:
REALLY getting tired of Disney using their abandonment of the expanded universe to make a blatant and unnecessary changes. Apparently my pet peeve for this movie is the unnecessary need to change the Millenium Falcon, fight the fact that the YT 1300 had a pretty stock appearance. I get their money grabbing needs to change everything else, but they literally could have left that little detail alone and ran with it. It's like every one of these new movies that have come out have dangled something from the expanded universe in our faces and then shat on it, rub out faces in it, and then told us to swallow.

When Disney first bought out Star Wars I defended them because I enjoyed what they did with the Marvel Cinematic Universe. I had high hopes that they would finally get out of the Empire Era and start making movies about the Old Republic or even before. Or maybe we would finally get a movie purely from The Darkside perspective, for the forming of the Sith.

Now not only do I no longer expect it I'm not even sure if I'd want to see it.

Title: Solo: A Star Wars Story Official Trailer
Comment: This looks like a fun movie - I'm gonna check it out for sure. In my opinion The Last Jedi was pretty great in a lot of ways, I personally loved that it challenged expectations. So far I'm really happy with what Lucasfilm have done and are doing given the crazy pressure they must be under (mostly from so-called fans, to deliver their individual and highly specific vision of what these films and characters should be, oh and those shareholder $$$). A lot of the comments here, and the hate on display, is surprising and not at all what I'd expect from the Star Wars community of fans. It's like the haters haven't actually learned anything from watching the Lucas era films and incorporated any of that into how they conduct themselves as human beings, how sad is that!? It just comes off as puerile entitlement... What I observe when I watch behind the scenes footage (especially after watching the director and the Jedi documentary) is many talented individuals who deeply love Star Wars and are giving their all to honour Lucas' legacy, but also establish a new trajectory. Of course if you really don't enjoy these films, that's perfectly fine. But it's too easy to just sit there and be so damned negative - I assume you are here because you are a Star Wars fan - which means you're better than that. Or you're a troll, in which case - meh, move along.

Comment: Absolutely no reason for the Falcon to look different. The YT-1300 is a very specific design and the Falcon received no major cosmetic alterations to that design ever in its entire existence. Even before it was in Lando's possession and known as the Falcon. Title: Solo: A Star Wars Story Official Trailer
Comment:
It seems tonally off in respects to the original films. Perhaps another example of a film that had too many cooks in the kitchen. Multiple directors and writers and rewrites and too much studio interference.  Of course I'm basing this off the trailers so I could be wrong. Guess we'll find out in May after Jeremy Jahns and Chris Stuckman review it..

Btw, I'm not a Star Wars fanatic, but if you're going to have a film marketed as a "Star Wars Story" it might be wise to do more than just fill it with familiar props and hire a director who's an old friend of the creator to replace two weaker directors. 

If they still plan on doing an Obi-Wan Kenobi stand-alone film, I really hope they don't go in this direction.. In fact, they should get the folks who wrote and directed Logan to do the Obi-Wan Kenobi stand-alone film.

IMHO
